<%# `update`, not `replace`: the result banner needs updating on every scan, repeatedly, without
    a page reload — `replace` swaps out the whole `#scan-result` element (the
    `.checkin-result-slot` wrapper carrying the spacing between it and the Scan button above) for
    whatever _result's own root happens to be that render, which has no id/class of its own to be
    re-targeted by — confirmed live: the SECOND scan onward lost both the wrapper (so the banner
    sat flush against the Scan button, no gap) and the ability to update again at all (no element
    with id="scan-result" left in the DOM for a follow-up turbo_stream.replace to find). `update`
    replaces only the wrapper's *contents*, leaving the wrapper — id, class, spacing — in place
    across every subsequent scan. %>
<%= turbo_stream.update "scan-result" do %>
  <%= render "result", result: @result, print_result: @print_result %>
<% end %>
